You're the first person I've told.

254
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,070
I'm so sorry.

255
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,770
I feel like I've lost so much...

256
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:58,070
...that having this baby would change things,but...

257
00:22:00,180 --> 00:22:01,670
now that it's gone...

258
00:22:05,780 --> 00:22:07,970
...this isn't the life that I wanted.

259
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:14,970
Does this have anything to do
with what happened the day of your wedding?

260
00:22:21,580 --> 00:22:25,070
You told me you weren't gonna marry lex,
and then, all of a sudden,somehow...

261
00:22:26,780 --> 00:22:28,770
something changed your mind.What was it?

262
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:34,270
It was just wedding-day jitters,that's all.

263
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,470
Lana...

264
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:40,870
it was more than that.

265
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:47,070
You don't need to be afraid.Whatever you need --

266
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:50,570
clark, I need you to stop worrying about me.

267
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:53,670
It's okay, really.

268
00:22:56,680 --> 00:23:00,270
I'm going to get through this
like I always do.

269
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:17,270
When my wife ends up in the hospital,
that means you've made a grave mistake.

270
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,670
I didn't mean for anyone else to get hurt.

271
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,470
I just wanted you to suffer.

272
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:27,870
Well, clearly chloe gets her brazenness
from her mother's side.

273
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:32,370
But as meddlesome as she can be,
I've actually come to admire her.

274
00:23:34,180 --> 00:23:35,770
That's what makes this so difficult.

275
00:23:35,780 --> 00:23:38,170
You stay away from my daughter.

276
00:23:38,180 --> 00:23:40,470
Oh, it's too late for that.

277
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,370
Clark?

278
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,170
Clark?

279
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:57,370
Clark?

280
00:23:57,880 --> 00:24:00,970
- Hey. How's lana?
- She's okay.

281
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:02,470
What'd you find out?

282
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:07,470
My mom was playing simon says with that guy
at the mansion,which means she's desperate.

283
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,870
He told mewhere I could find her.

284
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:09,970
Can we trust him?

285
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:12,670
Well, there is an old, abandoned hospital
on paper mill road,

286
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,670
just like he said,and it's owned by --

287
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:15,970
luthorcorp.

288
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:18,270
It's probably another 33.1 franchise.

289
00:24:18,280 --> 00:24:19,470
I was gonna go check it out,

290
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:22,570
but I thought it would be more wise
for me to come get my army of one.

291
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:33,870
Chloe, get out of smallville, sweetheart,
as fast as you can.

292
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,970
- Where you going?
- I have to leave.

293
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:40,870
- Chloe --
- let me go, clark.

294
00:24:41,580 --> 00:24:42,670
I have to leave town.

295
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:44,970
I'm not letting you go anywhere.

296
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:48,770
What's going on?

297
00:24:48,780 --> 00:24:50,570
It's your mom trying to control you again.

298
00:24:50,580 --> 00:24:52,570
Oh, my god.

299
00:24:52,580 --> 00:24:53,970
Are you okay?

300
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:55,870
Yeah, I'm just dizzy.

301
00:24:57,380 --> 00:25:00,270
- Can you get me a glass of water?
- Yeah.

302
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:16,670
Sorry, clark,but I have no choice.

303
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:18,770
Please...don't do this.

304
00:25:21,580 --> 00:25:23,770
It's the only way I'll be able
to get out of smallville.

305
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:56,770
STOP

306
00:25:59,980 --> 00:26:01,570
- I need to get through.
- Sorry, miss.

307
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:06,170
No.You don't understand.
I need to leave town right now.

308
00:26:06,280 --> 00:26:08,270
I'm afraid we're gonna have to reroute you.

309
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:09,870
What are you --

310
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:28,170
Mom?

311
00:26:34,780 --> 00:26:36,070
Mom!

312
00:26:40,080 --> 00:26:41,170
Chloe.

313
00:26:48,580 --> 00:26:51,470
You're even more beautiful than I remember.

314
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:54,270
I can't believe you're awake
and you're talking.

315
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,870
I thought I'd never
get to speak to you again.

316
00:26:57,380 --> 00:26:59,270
Honey,you shouldn't be here.

317
00:26:59,980 --> 00:27:01,970
This is all my fault.

318
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:03,270
No, it's not.

319
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:05,970
You needed my help.

320
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:12,770
just like when you were little.

321
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:13,970
What?

322
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:20,870
Remember when you were 8
and you hurt your hands?

323
00:27:21,180 --> 00:27:23,170
Yeah, how could I forget?

324
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:25,370
I had to wear those bandages for weeks.

325
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:27,570
You know, I've never
played kickball since then.

326
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:30,270
You didn't hurt your hand playing kickball.

327
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:38,470
You came home from school,

328
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,570
and your hands were all covered in ink.

329
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:46,070
So, I told you to go wash your hands,
and instead, you --

330
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:49,270
you went to play with your computer.

331
00:27:50,580 --> 00:27:52,570
I was so frustrated.

332
00:27:54,580 --> 00:27:58,570
I sent you to go wash your hands

333
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:01,970
and scrub them till all the ink was gone.

334
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:06,270
Mom, what are you saying?

335
00:28:06,780 --> 00:28:10,370
I found you in the bathroom.

336
00:28:11,380 --> 00:28:12,870
There was blood everywhere.

337
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:15,170
You had scrubbed your hands raw.

338
00:28:16,580 --> 00:28:18,570
That's why I left --

339
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:20,770
to protect you from me.

340
00:28:24,780 --> 00:28:27,670
And now I have to protect you from lex luthor.

341
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:31,170
This man that brought you here --

342
00:28:31,180 --> 00:28:32,970
he knows you're infected.

343
00:28:33,580 --> 00:28:35,170
You have to get out of here.

344
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,570
No. We have to get out of here.

345
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:40,170
Mom, you can control people with powers.

346
00:28:40,180 --> 00:28:42,670
Is there anyone in here
whose ability could free us?

347
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:50,170
I'd love to.

348
00:28:50,780 --> 00:28:52,970
Yes, lunch before the meeting is perfect.

349
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:54,470
Okay. Bye-bye.

350
00:28:57,180 --> 00:28:58,170
Clark!

351
00:29:04,180 --> 00:29:05,970
Sweetie, wake up!

352
00:29:06,180 --> 00:29:08,270
Clark!

353
00:29:09,180 --> 00:29:11,170
- Mom?
- Oh, baby.

354
00:29:18,580 --> 00:29:19,870
No more experiments.

355
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:20,770
Keep walking.

356
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:25,170
Help! I need help in here, please! Help!

357
00:29:28,380 --> 00:29:29,970
My mom -- she's sick.She needs a doctor.

358
00:29:29,980 --> 00:29:30,580
What's wrong?

359
00:29:30,590 --> 00:29:32,270
I don't know,but you have to help her.

360
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:35,670
Hey! Hey!What the hell?

361
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:37,470
Mom! Mom!

362
00:29:42,380 --> 00:29:45,370
Protect me and my daughter.Set us free.

363
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:53,570
Stop!

364
00:29:59,180 --> 00:30:00,570
Hold it right there.

365
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:13,170
Mom!

366
00:30:13,180 --> 00:30:14,370
Chloe!

367
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:16,070
Go! Get out of here!

368
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:18,870
Take her back to the cell.

369
00:30:21,480 --> 00:30:25,570
Chloe, whatever you have to do,get out now.

370
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:44,570
Lex, get out of my way.

371
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:47,170
I'm sorry.I can't do that.

372
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:56,070
Don't let your mother make you
do something you'll later --

373
00:31:30,780 --> 00:31:32,870
Hey!I brought sandwiches.

374
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:36,170
I don't know which ones you like, mom,
so I bought one of each.

375
00:31:36,180 --> 00:31:37,370
I don't think your mom's hungry.

376
00:31:37,380 --> 00:31:39,270
Have you talked to oliver?

377
00:31:39,380 --> 00:31:41,870
He said that he would set up a safe place
for her to stay in star city.

378
00:32:05,980 --> 00:32:08,470
Mom?

379
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,970
Mom?

380
00:32:13,980 --> 00:32:17,370
I-I wanted to see a blue sky...

381
00:32:18,780 --> 00:32:19,970
one last time.

382
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:23,970
Well, there will be plenty of blue skies
where you're going, mom.

383
00:32:23,980 --> 00:32:26,070
You're not gonna be locked inside anymore.

384
00:32:27,280 --> 00:32:28,670
Sweetheart...

385
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:32,870
...I'm slipping back.

386
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:37,170
The drug that lex used on your mom --
it only lasts 24 hours,

387
00:32:37,780 --> 00:32:39,470
or else she won't stay lucid.

388
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,870
Chloe, she doesn't have much time left.

389
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:45,370
Well, I'll go talk to lex.
I'll make a deal with him.

390
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:49,570
No.No deals with that man.

391
00:32:49,580 --> 00:32:50,770
I can't allow it.

392
00:32:50,780 --> 00:32:52,770
Mom, I already lost you once.
I'm not gonna do it again.

393
00:32:52,780 --> 00:32:56,270
If this drug is out there,
I can get it, trust me.

394
00:32:56,980 --> 00:32:59,870
I have some pretty amazing
resources at my disposal.

395
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:08,270
Being with you again.

396
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:15,770
...It's the greatest gift
I could have ever been given.

397
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:20,470
But I'm dangerous, chloe.

398
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,570
No, mom.That's not true.

399
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:28,270
My ability to control people with powers,

400
00:33:28,980 --> 00:33:32,670
it's like I'm a human weapon.

401
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:36,170
And I-I can't --I can't allow it.

402
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:38,670
But, mom, it doesn't have to be like this.

403
00:33:42,980 --> 00:33:46,770
My little cub reporter.

404
00:33:49,780 --> 00:33:51,270
This...

405
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:53,770
this belongs...

406
00:33:55,780 --> 00:33:57,570
...to you.

407
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:59,570
No, mom. Please.

408
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:03,270
Please don't go, mom --

409
00:34:03,580 --> 00:34:06,170
not yet, not again.

410
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:18,270
I...

411
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:22,070
...love you...

412
00:34:25,380 --> 00:34:27,770
...chlo-- chloe.

413
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:39,370
I love you, too, mom.

414
00:35:12,480 --> 00:35:15,270
"Luthorcorp crimesagainst humanity."

415
00:35:16,980 --> 00:35:18,070
That's catchy.

416
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:23,070
Too bad it'll never make it to print.

417
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:30,570
Lex, I'm tired of playing hardball
or softball or any ball,for that matter.

418
00:35:31,380 --> 00:35:32,470
Game's over.

419
00:35:35,380 --> 00:35:37,670
I'll tell you, your audacity's impressive, chloe,

420
00:35:38,580 --> 00:35:41,370
